                  <span class="commtext c00">Advanced Scanners | Principal Software Engineer | Austin, TX
Advanced Scanners is a recently funded seed-stage medical device company bringing its unique IP to solve real problems in surgical navigation for patients undergoing open brain surgery. We are looking for a strong software development engineer to build the next generation of medical software.
You&#x27;ll lead a small software development team, and have responsibility for the analysis, specification, design and verification of software for medical applications in a regulated environment using FDA-acceptable tools and methods.
Apply your technical expertise towards developing world-class algorithms and systems solutions using software engineering tools to solve complex technical problems related to optical imaging and surgical navigation. You&#x27;ll participate in technical reviews, select the most promising concepts, implement advances in current state-of-the-art technology, in the areas of image processing, machine learning, artificial intelligence, and identify opportunities for productivity and quality improvement. You should have experience in C# or C++, and imaging development on GPUs.
Gory details about what we do at <a href="https:&#x2F;&#x2F;www.advancedscanners.com" rel="nofollow">https:&#x2F;&#x2F;www.advancedscanners.com</a>. Contact Aaron Bernstein at aaronb@advancedscanners.com</span>
